{"parse":{"title":"Public Force","pageid":19492783,"revid":599815825,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>A <b>Public Force</b> is a force which has a legitimate and legalised use of physical force in order to serve the public interests. \n</p><p>The term is broad and loosely defined. Public force could be used to refer to either police or military forces.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Original_use_of_the_term\">Original use of the term</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Public_Force&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Original use of the term\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The first use of the concept of a <b>public force</b>, in French <i><b>Force Publique</b></i>, is in the <a href=\"/wiki/Declaration_of_the_Rights_of_Man_and_of_the_Citizen\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Declaration of the Rights of Man and of the Citizen\">Declaration of the Rights of Man and of the Citizen</a> of 1789.<i> </i>\n</p><p><i> <b>Article XIII</b> - For the maintenance of the public force and for the expenditures of administration, a common contribution is indispensable; it must be equally distributed between all the citizens, by reason of their faculties [i.e., ability to pay].</i>\n</p><p>The declaration sought to regulate the relationship between the citizen and the legitimate use of violence. In contrast to similar declarations of rights from <a href=\"/wiki/Anglo-Saxon\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Anglo-Saxon\">Anglo-Saxon</a> countries, the emphasis is on the citizen's duty to contribute to the existence of such a force, rather than on the citizen's rights vis-a-vis such a force.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Further_use_of_the_term\">Further use of the term</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Public_Force&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Further use of the term\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The concept was also used in other countries, e.g. in Thomas Jefferson's <a href=\"https://en.wikisource.org/wiki/Thomas_Jefferson%27s_Sixth_State_of_the_Union_Address\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"s:Thomas Jefferson&#39;s Sixth State of the Union Address\">Sixth State of the Union Address</a>.\n</p><p><i><b>Force Publique</b></i> was the title of the colonial army and gendarmerie of the <a href=\"/wiki/Congo_Free_State\" title=\"Congo Free State\">Congo Free State</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Belgian_Congo\" title=\"Belgian Congo\">Belgian Congo</a> from 1885-1960 (<i>see: <b><a href=\"/wiki/Public_Force_(Congo)\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Public Force (Congo)\">Public Force (Congo)</a></b></i>). \n</p><p>The term has been used as a designation for police or military forces in other countries, e.g. <a href=\"/wiki/Panama\" title=\"Panama\">Panama</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Costa_Rica\" title=\"Costa Rica\">Costa Rica</a>, and is commonly used as a conceptual term in several countries, e.g. <a href=\"/wiki/France\" title=\"France\">France</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Morocco\" title=\"Morocco\">Morocco</a>.\n</p>\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nParsed by mw1339\nCached time: 20180901125550\nCache expiry: 1900800\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.012 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.015 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 8/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 0/1500000\nPost\u2010expand include size: 0/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 0/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 2/40\nExpensive parser function count: 0/500\nUnstrip recursion depth: 0/20\nUnstrip post\u2010expand size: 0/5000000 bytes\nNumber of Wikibase entities loaded: 0/400\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%    0.000      1 -total\n-->\n\n<!-- Saved in parser cache with key enwiki:pcache:idhash:19492783-0!canonical and timestamp 20180901125550 and revision id 599815825\n -->\n</div>"},"langlinks":[{"lang":"es","url":"https://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Force_Publique","langname":"Spanish","autonym":"espa\u00f1ol","*":"Force Publique"},{"lang":"fr","url":"https://fr.wikipedia.org/wiki/Force_publique","langname":"French","autonym":"fran\u00e7ais","*":"Force publique"},{"lang":"ko","url":"https://ko.wikipedia.org/wiki/%EA%B3%B5%EA%B6%8C%EB%A0%A5","langname":"Korean","autonym":"\ud55c\uad6d\uc5b4","*":"\uacf5\uad8c\ub825"},{"lang":"hu","url":"https://hu.wikipedia.org/wiki/Force_Publique","langname":"Hungarian","autonym":"magyar","*":"Force Publique"},{"lang":"nl","url":"https://nl.wikipedia.org/wiki/Force_Publique","langname":"Dutch","autonym":"Nederlands","*":"Force Publique"},{"lang":"ja","url":"https://ja.wikipedia.org/wiki/%E5%85%AC%E5%AE%89%E8%BB%8D_(%E3%82%B3%E3%83%B3%E3%82%B4)","langname":"Japanese","autonym":"\u65e5\u672c\u8a9e","*":"\u516c\u5b89\u8ecd (\u30b3\u30f3\u30b4)"}],"categories":[{"sortkey":"","*":"Political_theories"},{"sortkey":"","*":"History_of_human_rights"},{"sortkey":"","*":"Violence"}],"links":[{"ns":0,"exists":"","*":"Anglo-Saxon"},{"ns":0,"exists":"","*":"Belgian Congo"},{"ns":0,"exists":"","*":"Congo Free State"},{"ns":0,"exists":"","*":"Costa Rica"},{"ns":0,"exists":"","*":"Declaration of the Rights of Man and of the Citizen"},{"ns":0,"exists":"","*":"France"},{"ns":0,"exists":"","*":"Morocco"},{"ns":0,"exists":"","*":"Panama"},{"ns":0,"exists":"","*":"Public Force (Congo)"}],"templates":[],"images":[],"externallinks":[],"sections":[{"toclevel":1,"level":"2","line":"Original use of the term","number":"1","index":"1","fromtitle":"Public_Force","byteoffset":246,"anchor":"Original_use_of_the_term"},{"toclevel":1,"level":"2","line":"Further use of the term","number":"2","index":"2","fromtitle":"Public_Force","byteoffset":1038,"anchor":"Further_use_of_the_term"}],"parsewarnings":[],"displaytitle":"Public Force","iwlinks":[{"prefix":"s","url":"https://en.wikisource.o